cope of a world not unlike our own, a world on the road to globalization. In its ports, we find a priceless cargo of information. Here are the first foreign descriptions of tea and porcelain, a panorama of unusual social practices, cannibal islands, and Indian holy men-a marvelous, mundane world, contained in the compass of a novella.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jun 2020) 0aChina - Description and travel. 0aIndiaxDescription and travelvEarly works to 1800. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Middle Eastern.2bisacsh1 aBenite, Zvi Ben-Dor1 aMackintosh-Smith, Tim40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479862054423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781479862054.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK